parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause a loss of braking ability, leading to accidents or near-misses, and potentially resulting in injury or death.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal travels to the floor with little or no resistance
the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual
the vehicle requires repeated pumping of the brake pedal to stop
the vehicle stalls out and loses braking and steering ability.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Improperly resurfaced brake rotors can cause uneven brake pad wear, leading to reduced braking performance and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle vibrates or pulsates when applying the brakes
the brake pedal feels uneven or spongy
the brakes make a grinding or screeching noise
the brake pads wear down unevenly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) can cause the vehicle to lose traction and control, leading to accidents or near-misses, and potentially resulting in injury or death.
symptoms: The vehicle's brakes fail to respond or engage
the vehicle's front end hits the curb or other obstacles
the ABS warning light illuminates on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rust and corrosion on the frame can compromise the structural integrity of the vehicle, leading to potential safety risks, including loss of control, accidents, or even collapse of the vehicle.
symptoms: Visible rust or corrosion on the frame
particularly at connection points such as the A-frame assembly
front cross member
or other areas exposed to moisture and salt; weakened or brittle frame components; potential for frame failure or collapse.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Tank Stress Cracks and Fuel Leakage
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature development of stress cracks in the fuel tank can cause fuel leakage, which can lead to fires, explosions, or other safety hazards, especially in the presence of an ignition source.
symptoms: Fuel leakage
fuel smell
fuel droplets or puddles under the vehicle
decreased fuel efficiency
engine stalling or difficulty starting.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Wheel Stud Corrosion and Insufficient Thread Engagement
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion of wheel studs and insufficient thread engagement can cause wheel weights to fly off while driving, leading to loss of control and potential accidents. Additionally, it can also cause wheels to come loose, resulting in wheel separation and accidents.
symptoms: Wheel weights flying off
wheels coming loose
lug nuts stripping
difficulty tightening lug nuts
corrosion on wheel studs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition coil can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or dies while driving
the engine misfires
the check engine light illuminates
the vehicle experiences a loss of power or hesitation.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty warm-up motor (EGR valve) can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or dies while driving
the engine misfires
the check engine light illuminates
the vehicle experiences a loss of power or hesitation.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the overdrive or power steering system can cause a loss of vehicle control, making it difficult to steer the vehicle, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences a loss of power steering assist
the steering wheel is difficult to turn
the vehicle pulls to one side while driving.
